    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels for Medium model risk. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against required level 3 due to single ASTM F1717 test protocol; risk accepted given quasi-static loading and low strain-rate sensitivity of Ti-6Al-4V. All three QoIs satisfy the <10% difference and E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criteria. Model credibility sufficient to support 510(k) regulatory submission for the non-cannulated pedicle screw design.",
